Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.97,0:01:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd better see some gratitude, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.61,0:01:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You showed up without so much as calling ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:01:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,telling me to join you on this stupid trip to Fukui,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.53,0:01:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and out of the kindness of my heart I agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, don't be so crabby. I'm paying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.70,0:02:07.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Where're we headed, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tiny island named Bikuni Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But most of the locals call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the island where the mermaid lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.60,0:02:20.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Bikuni Island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.50,0:02:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mermaid?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.04,0:02:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.60,0:02:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say there is an old lady on that island that eats memaid meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.40,0:02:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About 3 years ago, there was a big fuss about her,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.90,0:02:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she is an old lady who has lived forever, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.02,0:02:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.00,0:02:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I decided to come along
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because I wanted to learn the secret of her beauty & longevity!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.75,0:02:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.10,0:02:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to scare Heiji with those secrets, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.32,0:02:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk so loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.42,0:02:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That letter you got asking us to find the mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.93,0:02:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't just some idiot who wants to see one, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.20,0:02:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.21,0:02:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was only three lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:03:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,written in shaky handwriting...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.94,0:03:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mermaid is going to kill me! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.11,0:03:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is going to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give me a break,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.34,0:03:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,mermaids only exist in fairy tales,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,don't expect me to take you seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't believe they really exist either,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.50,0:03:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the name on the letter got my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The envelope was addressed to me but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the letter was written to Shinichi Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.95,0:03:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should be thanking me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it might be somebody from your past, that is why I brought you along!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.20,0:03:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,did you contact the person who sent the letter to confirm it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sender, Saori Kadowaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.52,0:03:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wrote the number for her cellular phone on the letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one answered after the second time I called,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.83,0:03:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the first time I called someone answered and hung up immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.58,0:03:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that first call though,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:03:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can still hear
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.40,0:04:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the sound coming from the other side of the receiver...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.10,0:04:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the sound of waves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.45,0:04:05.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a woman moaning...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.29,0:04:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be... do you think it was her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.65,0:04:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the memaid already killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saori Kadowaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.08,0:04:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Three days ago, she stopped coming in to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.92,0:04:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three days ago... That's around the time I got the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.94,0:04:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her neighbors think she took a boat to the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.10,0:04:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.85,0:04:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.33,0:04:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, gotta get ready for the festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.66,0:04:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.03,0:04:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The annual Dugong Festival is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.19,0:04:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to know more, try the souvenir shop on the corner. That's where Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lucky mermaid charm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.78,0:04:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a mermaid cell phone strap...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and special dugong buns...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.85,0:04:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This island's full of mermaids, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a dugong, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.00,0:05:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a mammal that lives in the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.77,0:05:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people say that that's the model for the mermaid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.20,0:05:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used to live in the southern part of Japan too, long ago, and it was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.90,0:05:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Believed that their meat was medical and could make you live a long life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Arrow of Dugong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.89,0:05:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... It's an amulet for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only three are given away each year,\Nat the annual Dugong Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} won an arrow at last year's festival, but she lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was terrified that the mermaid would curse her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mermaids, yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.97,0:05:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But mermaids do exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:45.41,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Naoko Kuroe (28)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NSouvenir Shop Clerk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Lady Mikoto ate the flesh of a mermaid and received immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Arrow of Dugong has her hair tied to it, and anyone who wins one can become immortal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:53.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Arrow of Dugong
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.43,0:05:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not surprised Saori ran away from the island after she lost her arrow. She could be cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.42,0:06:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.69,0:06:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a childhood friend of Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.18,0:06:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who's this Lady Mikoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head of the festival and matriarch of the Shimabukuro family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.84,0:06:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the icon of the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.55,0:06:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How old is this lady, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I've heard rumors that she's 100 or 200 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't believe me, why don't you go to the shrine for the festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The holy person's great-granddaughter, Kimie,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's also Saori's childhood friend should be there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.20,0:06:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we're being given the run around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.14,0:06:41.60,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Bikuni Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.03,0:06:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,200 years old? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:46.31,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kimie Shimabukuro (27)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NBikuni Shrine Maiden
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My great-grandmother is exactly 130 years old this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can check her birth certificate if you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.02,0:06:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because she's a little older than most, everyone exaggerates so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little older...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:57.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's old enough for the Guinness Book of World Records.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So where is yer old lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.16,0:07:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's in her room, blessing the three arrows that are going to be handed out at the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Lady Mikoto really {\i1}did{\i0} eat mermaid's flesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.85,0:07:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mermaids don't exist, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That story's a complete lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But the Arrow of Dugong...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My late mother told me it was originally the Arrow of Jugon, an amulet to ward off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:36.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Anti-Evil Arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:36.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,jugon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.95,0:07:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Great-Grandma started getting attention for her long life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.95,0:07:36.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Arrow of Dugong
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.95,0:07:36.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,jugon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.29,0:07:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,people around here renamed it the Arrow of Dugong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.05,0:07:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, with my father, at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.42,0:07:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandparents were lost at sea too before I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great-Grandma and I are the only members of the family left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you lost your whole family to the sea, then maybe there's somethin' to the legends!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.36,0:07:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the mainland with Saori just a few days ago and nothing happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.94,0:07:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.51,0:08:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were with Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.86,0:08:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.55,0:08:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the dentist and she came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.19,0:08:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't have a dentist on the island, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What state was she in when you saw her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.55,0:08:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was terrified because she'd lost that arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm cursed by the mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.45,0:08:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wouldn't believe the curse wasn't real.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.07,0:08:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just don't believe in Lady Mikoto's powers, do you, Kimie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:34.24,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toshimi Ebihara (27)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NDaughter of the Head of the Fishermen's Union
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the real deal! She really ate the flesh of a mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We even found a mermaid's corpse three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mermaid's corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wasn't it on television about 3 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The media played it up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.62,0:08:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know what you are talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.35,0:08:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.90,0:08:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bones were crushed in a very strange way, is was grotesque...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:08:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rokuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.59,0:09:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got nothing more to say to outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.61,0:09:08.11,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Rokuro Fukuyama (28)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.09,0:09:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for Saori,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.74,0:09:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why're you wasting time here?\NJust go to her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's if that drunk father of hers lets you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A girl's gone missing, and nobody's freakin' out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saori fights with her dad and runs away all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you take us to Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, after the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.10,0:09:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of festival is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People buy tickets,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and if the number on the ticket matches the number Great-Grandma draws,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.01,0:09:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they win an Arrow of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We call it a festival, but it's more like a lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.79,0:09:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.28,0:09:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you two give it a go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An elderly couple cancelled their ticket order this morning, so I've got two extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether you win or lose, it's all up to the Gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.75,0:10:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe, you'll be able to obtain eternal youth and beauty just like the rumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.00,0:10:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.69,0:10:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.03,0:10:30.76,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mikoto Shimabukuro (130)\NLady Mikoto
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.40,0:10:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's the holy person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.60,0:10:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The holy person is making her appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.10,0:10:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's Lady Mikoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.70,0:10:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's so tiny...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.90,0:10:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just an old lady in lotsa make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-She... set fire to the paper screens!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.58,0:10:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire is taking the shape of words!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.38,0:11:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The winning numbers are under the screens!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.91,0:11:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.18,0:11:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hooray! I'm so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.44,0:11:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-R-Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.96,0:11:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.50,0:11:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.12,0:11:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Attention, winners.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time has come to bestow the Arrows of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.30,0:11:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please follow me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the Waterfall of the Mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.73,0:11:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will the three fortunate ones please come forth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.07,0:11:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.30,0:11:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.05,0:11:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.69,0:11:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there one more winner here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:12:01.25,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Benzo Kadowaki (52)\NSaori's Father\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.24,0:11:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.65,0:12:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that girl won.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.82,0:12:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I don't see her around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.78,0:12:14.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But we soon found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.03,0:12:16.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}at the foot of the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.20,0:12:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May fortune light the path for these three!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.59,0:12:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long, black hair wafting...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On a slim body that sways...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.00,0:12:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it most certainly looked like...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.52,0:12:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mermaid swimming up the waterfall,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiny & blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.63,0:12:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it was a lifeless body...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Toshimi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.89,0:13:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or did somebody...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.58,0:13:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might not be either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the rope that strangled Toshimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's part of the rope fence we strung here to keep people from falling in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.64,0:13:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell into the river in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.93,0:13:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She grabbed the rope, but the stake slipped out of the mud and the rope wrapped around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't it seem fishy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The festival was still goin' on at the foot of the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.01,0:13:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why'd she go wanderin' into the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she was looking for the mermaid's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.86,0:13:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a mermaid's grave somewhere in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It contains the bones of the mermaid who was found three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.14,0:13:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the night of the festival, when the shrine's warehouse burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.37,0:14:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Toshimi was always curious about that grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.20,0:14:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on just a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.58,0:14:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You keep talkin' about mermaid this and mermaid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't {\i1}really{\i0} a mermaid, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.26,0:14:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.75,0:14:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what the islanders believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the police from the mainland thought it was the body of a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.69,0:14:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could it be an ordinary woman? The bones only went down to the waist!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They did?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.02,0:14:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A couple of large pillars in the warehouse had crushed the body from the waist down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.85,0:14:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then we moved the pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The leg bones that should've been on the other side of the pillars...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.59,0:14:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That's hard to believe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.87,0:14:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.55,0:14:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the media made a big fuss broadcasting that a mermaid's body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.70,0:14:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And our holy person bacame famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the police thought it was a woman's body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said a disgruntled tourist must've broken into the warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.41,0:14:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,looking for an extra arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,lit a candle, and accidentally started a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a year passed without anyone claiming the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we decided to give it a proper burial.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.16,0:15:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we ran into another problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grave robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.40,0:15:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid tourists started trying to dig up the body and steal the bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.40,0:15:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they heard that mermaid bones were the elixir of eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Great-Grandmother had someone move the grave to a secret spot in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did she ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All she said was that it was someone she trusted very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.95,0:15:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, whether this was murder, suicide or accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.40,0:15:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we can't do anything but take Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} down and wait for the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.07,0:15:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was murder, Toshimi was asking for trouble, coming up here alone in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.55,0:15:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a thing to say about your fiancée!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.90,0:15:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.69,0:16:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our parents arranged that without our consent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.27,0:16:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now my mom and dad are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.43,0:16:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.91,0:16:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.29,0:16:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimi's father, Ebihara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NHe's head of the local fishermen's union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, did you contact the Fukui prefectural police?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.52,0:16:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but they won't be able to come out for a while. The sea's too rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.54,0:16:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, for the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.92,0:16:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great! This is perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means the killer's gotta stay put on the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.40,0:16:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.16,0:16:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't even decided if this was murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.27,0:16:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.45,0:16:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An inner tube?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} and I found it stuck in the river, between the waterfall and the river mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.63,0:16:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm guessin' our culprit knocked Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out at the top of the waterfall,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:16:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wrapped the rope around her neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,an' floated her down the river to fake a hangin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was last seen at the shrine two hours before her body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes less'n an hour to climb to the top of the waterfall an' back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:15.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was plenty of time for {\i1}anyone{\i0} to kill her an' make it look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.43,0:17:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the killer is still somewhere on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.49,0:17:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.65,0:17:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer will be cought in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Heiji moves his hat around, he's turned his switch on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.55,0:17:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's ready to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.27,0:17:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must've fallen in love with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.10,0:17:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm no match for you... if we become rivals...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.15,0:17:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ka-Kazuha...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.97,0:17:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.24,0:17:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.72,0:17:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Toshimi was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better not let that person out of your sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about Saori's drunk of a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.25,0:18:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to go to Saori's home now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take you since I promised you earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.15,0:18:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him in that condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.07,0:18:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt he'll be much help through.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.05,0:18:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.55,0:18:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to meet the holy person!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.31,0:18:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy this house is old...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.98,0:18:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like they're making too much money from these dugong arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.96,0:18:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those platelets cost 5 yen a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.41,0:18:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? 5 yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people in this island said the price has been the same
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.51,0:18:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since they can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.35,0:18:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are 108 number platelets in a huge box
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.56,0:18:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And everyone lines up then pulls one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the old woman picks the 3 winning numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's taking the old lady so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.42,0:18:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she'll come down to answer questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but she's tired from the festival, so she might not stay long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.72,0:19:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you the ones who wanted to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:10.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Without her make-up, she's an ogre!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.19,0:19:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.32,0:19:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wondering how you chose the winning numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.88,0:19:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At random.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.79,0:19:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a while, I picked the winning numbers from the horse races!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.42,0:19:28.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.19,0:19:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why're ya so stingy with the arrows? You oughta give away more than three!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.70,0:19:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only have so much hair on my head to tie to the arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.75,0:19:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great-Grandma! Your bath's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. If that's all, I'd like to take my bath and go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait! I still have a quest—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You there... Young girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.39,0:19:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one with your hair tied back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.86,0:19:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.49,0:20:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Arrow of Dugong is a charm to ward off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let go of it, and evil will fall upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.87,0:20:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Men will return to dust and become heartless devils.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.20,0:20:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Women will return to water and become speechless mermaids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.28,0:20:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't ever let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.55,0:20:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even her voice sounds wrinkly and she's so pale!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She looks like she could drop dead any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.00,0:20:35.46,Character Card,,0,0,0,,The Next Day\NEbihara House
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.89,0:20:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't ya glad we brought our school uniforms?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.23,0:20:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are ya sure we're supposed to be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.10,0:20:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it! It's the perfect chance to snoop around!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.94,0:20:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop smiling like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.05,0:20:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Toshimi's wake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.95,0:20:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.56,0:20:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,did you bring the arrow with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.95,0:20:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I certainly did!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.15,0:20:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.65,0:21:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.15,0:21:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he's already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.44,0:21:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came too, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.64,0:21:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er... Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kadowaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't go home yesterday. Did you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.53,0:21:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but I heard he was picking fights with tourists at the local tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.63,0:21:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drinkin' all night, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.85,0:21:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.85,0:21:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NHer name was in the guestbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Naoko here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.30,0:21:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's probably in the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.45,0:21:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go check
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.65,0:21:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.37,0:21:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.51,0:21:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? You afraid of thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.30,0:21:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.86,0:21:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's someone outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.56,0:22:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.22,0:22:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.41,0:22:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.60,0:22:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's someone outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.41,0:22:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.07,0:22:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...!
